from PyPDF2 import PdfReader
import io

# Attempt to read the PDF file using a different approach
try:
    with open(file_path, 'rb') as file:
        pdf_reader = PdfReader(file)
        text_content = []
        for page in pdf_reader.pages:
            text_content.append(page.extract_text())
            
    # Combine all text content
    full_text_alternative = " ".join(text_content)

import PyPDF2

# Open the PDF file
file_path = '/mnt/data/00000'
pdf_file = open(file_path, 'rb')

# Initialize PDF reader
pdf_reader = PyPDF2.PdfReader(pdf_file)

# Get the number of pages
num_pages = len(pdf_reader.pages)

# Extract text from all pages
text_content = []
for page_number in range(num_pages):
    # Extract text from page
    page = pdf_reader.pages[page_number]
    text_content.append(page.extract_text())

# Close the PDF file
pdf_file.close()

# Join the text content from all pages
full_text = " ".join(text_content)

# Display the first 1000 characters to understand the content
full_text[:1000]
